ZCZC GE80
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 122300 UTC
ON TUESDAY EVENING A LARGE DOMINANT REGION OF HIGH PRESSURE REMAINS SLOW-MOV
OVER THE UK AND ACROSS MOST OF NERN EUROPE. MEANWHILE A LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM
LIES TO THE W OF IBERIA AND IS SLWY MOV E. A SECOND LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM LIES
TO THE NW OF ICELAND AND IS ALSO SLWY MOV E. THIS SYNOPTIC SYSTEM REMAINS
LARGELY SIMILAR AND PERSISTENT THROUGH TO WEDNESDAY WHEN THE HIGH PRESSURE
SYSTEM OVER MOST OF EUROPE MOVS AWAY TO THE E AS THE LOW PRESSURE CENTRES
FILL. ON THURSDAY ANOTHER LOW DEVELOPS TO THE W OF IBERIA AND IS SLWY MOV
E INTO THURSDAY. STRG WINDS AND POSS GALES WILL AFFECT NWERN AREAS PARTICULARLY
FAIR ISLE AND VIKING THROUGH TUESDAY THEN SPREADING FURTHER E AND PERSISTING
THROUGH EARLY WEDNESDAY. LATE ON WEDNESDAY THESE STRG WINDS WILL EASE AND
THEN REMAIN BELOW FCST CRITERIA ON THURSDAY
